<article class="regular">

<h2>shred</h2>
<p>When you <em>really</em> want to delete a file, and make it very hard to recover, <code>shred</code> can come in handy:</p>

<pre><code>shred -u -z -n 10 plan-for-world-domination.txt
</code></pre>

<p>The above will overwrite your <code>plan-for-world-domination.txt</code> file with random ones and zeros 10 times, remove the file and finally overwrite it with zeros (in a bid to hide the fact you&#8217;ve shredded the file).</p>

<p><small>Needless to say, <code>shred</code> should be used with caution.</small></p>










